{
  "img": "Art%20-%20Items/swords/sword_tech_katana_saber_glow_blade.webp",
  "name": "Decap A Tater 3.0",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This blade is forged of a Glaucite alloy that is beyond modifcation by most smithies in the Inner Sea. Scrying spells cast upon it indicate it is over 7000 years old and does not originate on Golarion.</p><p>The blade has an unknown power-source and radiates no magic or external energy at all until swung or thrust in skillful use. The blade exhibits a soft blue-white glow while in use but this effect is not bright enougt to be seen any distance away.</p><p>It functions as a +1 keen Wakazashi or Shortsword. Due to it's laser-sharp blade that never needs to be sharpened, it bypasses DR as if it is adamantine.</p><img src=\"Art%20-%20Items/swords/sword_tech_katana_saber_glow_blade.webp\" />",
      "instructions": "",
      "unidentified": "<p>These short, slender blades are between 1 to 2 feet long. They are primarily used as back-up weapons, to decapitate defeated enemies, or to commit seppuku (ritual suicide) as a matter of honor. These blades are specifically worn by samurai and are intended to be paired with a katana. Together, this set of blades is referred to as a daisho.</p>"
    },
